4 Sec. 2. 12 MRSA §6072-E is enacted to read:
5 §6072-E. Limited-purpose license for aquaculture nursery and husbandry activities
6 1. License required. A person may not engage in the activities authorized under this
7 section without a current limited-purpose license for aquaculture nursery and husbandry
8 activities or a lease issued under this Part authorizing the activities. For the purposes of this
9 section, "husbandry" means specific activities designed to care for, manage and improve
10 marine organisms. "Husbandry" is distinct from culture, which includes the production and
11 development of marine organisms.
12 2. Licensed activities. The holder of a limited-purpose license for aquaculture nursery
13 and husbandry activities may:
14 A. Place marine organisms in early life stages, before sale to another person or before
15 further deployment to an aquaculture site pursuant to section 6072, 6072-A, 6072-B or
16 6072-C, in aquaculture gear or equipment at a site below the mean low-water mark in
17 the coastal waters of the State to engage in certain aquaculture activities that meet the
18 criteria established in subsection 3 and in rules adopted by the commissioner;
19 B. Conduct husbandry activities specific in nature and short in duration, before further
20 deployment to an aquaculture site pursuant to section 6072, 6072-A or 6072-B or a
21 license pursuant to 6072-C, using aquaculture gear or equipment at a site below the
22 mean low-water mark in the coastal waters of the State to engage in certain aquaculture
23 activities that meet the criteria established in subsection 3 and in rules adopted by the
24 commissioner; and
25 C. Deploy marine organisms in early life stages to a site other than the aquaculture site
26 identified in the lease pursuant to section 6072, 6072-A, 6072-B or 6072-C if the lease
27 holder is a municipal shellfish management committee established pursuant to section
28 6671 or a municipal officer for a municipal project.
29 3. Criteria. The commissioner, or staff designated in writing by the commissioner,
30 may issue a limited-purpose license for aquaculture nursery and husbandry activities if:
31 A. The proposed activity generates no discharge into coastal waters;
32 B. The applicant has an existing aquaculture lease pursuant to section 6072, 6072-A or
33 6072-B or a license pursuant to 6072-C, unless the applicant is a municipal shellfish
34 management committee established pursuant to section 6671 or a municipal officer for
35 a municipal project;
36 C. The applicant is using a source of stock approved by the commissioner;
37 D. The applicant proposes to use aquaculture gear or equipment approved by the
38 commissioner under the rules adopted pursuant to subsection 11;
39 E. The gear or equipment, excluding mooring equipment, does not cover more than
40 1,600 square feet of area and does not present an unreasonable impediment to safe
41 navigation;
