1 F. Include documentation that riparian owners within 300 feet of the proposed activity
2 have been notified of the license application and proposed activity; and
3 G. Include documentation that the municipality has been notified of the license
4 application.
5 License sites that are used for nursery and husbandry activities must also include in the
6 application a detailed description of specific activities to be conducted on the site and the
7 duration a marine organism will be located at the site for specific nursery and husbandry
8 activities. The maximum duration may not exceed 6 months.
9 7. Fee. Except as provided in subsection 8, the application fee for a limited-purpose
10 license for aquaculture nursery and husbandry activities is $400. The application fee is
11 nonrefundable. All fees collected under this subsection must be deposited in the
12 Aquaculture Research Fund established in section 6081.
13 8. Fee exemptions. The commissioner may not assess an application fee for a limited-
14 purpose license for aquaculture nursery and husbandry activities that is issued to:
15 A. A municipal shellfish management committee established pursuant to section 6671,
16 if the organisms cultured on the license site are not used for commercial purposes; or
17 B. A municipal officer for a municipal project, if the organisms cultured on the license
18 site are not used for commercial purposes.
19 9. Prohibition; molesting gear. A person other than a marine patrol officer, an
20 aquaculture inspector authorized by the commissioner or the licensee may not utilize, raise,
21 lift, transfer, possess or in any manner molest any approved aquaculture gear or equipment
22 that is deployed under a current limited-purpose license for aquaculture nursery and
23 husbandry activities.
24 10. Prohibition; taking product. A person other than a marine patrol officer, an
25 aquaculture inspector authorized by the commissioner or the licensee may not take any
26 marine organism grown on the license site in accordance with applicable rules.
27 11. Rules. The commissioner shall adopt rules to implement this section, including,
28 but not limited to, rules establishing the type of gear and equipment that is approved
29 aquaculture gear and equipment for the purposes of a limited-purpose license for
30 aquaculture nursery and husbandry activities, minimum standards for maintaining gear and
31 equipment, methods of gear and equipment identification and license application and
32 review procedures. The commissioner may adopt rules to limit the period of the year during
33 which license applications may be submitted. Rules adopted under this subsection are
34 routine technical rules pursuant to Title 5, chapter 375, subchapter 2-A.
35 12. Violation; restitution. A person who violates this section commits a civil violation
36 for which a fine of not less than $100 for each violation may be adjudged. If a person
37 violates subsection 9 by cutting any lines or marker buoys or intentionally damaging
38 approved aquaculture gear and equipment, the court shall also:
39 A. Order that person to pay to the owner of the approved aquaculture gear and
40 equipment that was cut or damaged an amount equal to twice the replacement value of
41 the gear and equipment that was lost or damaged as a result of the cutting or damaging
42 action; and
