1 B. Direct that person to provide the commissioner, upon making full payment as
2 ordered by the court, proof of that payment.
3 13. Reporting requirement; confidentiality. A holder of a limited-purpose license
4 for aquaculture nursery and husbandry activities shall annually submit to the department a
5 cultivation report for the past year. Information provided in cultivation reports submitted
6 by a license holder under this subsection is considered confidential information reported to
7 the commissioner pursuant to section 6173.
8 Sec. 3. 12 MRSA §6072-F is enacted to read:
9 §6072-F. Lease amendments
10 1. Lease amendment; prohibition. For the purposes of this section, "lease
11 amendment" means the authorized addition of species, gear, equipment and structure and
12 resultant modifications to operations to an existing lease issued under section 6072 or
13 6072-A. A lease amendment is not an adjudicatory proceeding. A lease issued under
14 section 6072-A for commercial research and development may not be amended. An
15 existing lease that does not allow discharge may not be amended to include operational
16 modifications that would result in the reclassification that allows discharge by the
17 commissioner pursuant to the lease. All fees collected under this section must be deposited
18 in the Aquaculture Management Fund established in section 6072-D.
19 2. Species. The holder of a lease under this subchapter must apply to the commissioner
20 to add a specific species and make resultant operational modifications to the holder's lease
21 site. The decision by the commissioner to authorize the addition of a species must be based
22 on factors, including, but not limited to, the source of stock. The commissioner may not
23 authorize the addition of a species that would cause the holder of the lease to violate any
24 existing condition of the lease. The commissioner shall establish by rule the process for
25 adding species to a lease. The commissioner shall establish by rule a nonrefundable fee for
26 applying to add species to a lease that may not exceed $200.
27 3. Gear. The holder of a lease under this subchapter must apply to the commissioner
28 to add different gear categories and make resultant operational modifications to the lease
29 site if the holder has held the lease for at least one year and the lease included authorization
30 for the bottom gear category only. The commissioner may not authorize the addition of
31 gear categories that would cause the holder of the lease to violate any existing condition of
32 the lease. Leases that were originally authorized without gear are not eligible to apply to
33 add gear under this subsection. The commissioner shall establish by rule the process for
34 adding different gear categories to a lease. The commissioner shall establish by rule a
35 nonrefundable fee for applying to add different gear categories to a lease that may not
36 exceed $500. The rules must provide for notice of proposed additions of different gear
37 categories to the public, riparian landowners and the municipality in which the lease is
38 located and an opportunity to submit written comments on the proposal. The replacement
39 of previously authorized gear does not require a lease amendment as long as the
40 replacement gear is substantially similar to the previously authorized gear. The
41 commissioner may not grant a lease amendment under this subsection that unreasonably
42 interferes with the conditions under section 6072, subsection 7-A.
43 4. Equipment; structure. The holder of a lease under this subchapter must apply to
44 the commissioner to add equipment or structure and make resultant operational
45 modifications to the holder's lease site if the holder has held the lease for at least one year
